May 17 2006	Hotel OK not keen on the area	We stayed here for three nights.When we arrived the receptionist made a big deal about the fact that we had been upgraded free of charge to a fireplace room. We had no idea that we weren't getting one or that they were available but it seemed a fair deal......that was until we got to the room. I knew as soon as we stepped out of the lift that we were on a smoking floor and crossed my fingers that the room wasn't a smoking room. It was to no avail. The room although nice enough could have been great if it wasn't for the fact it was a smokers room! All the fabric items (curtains, cushions etc.) just had that nicotine smell and they didn't feel great to the touch either. We should have checked when we were given the room at check in, but we didn't and we suffered for it for our stay.That said, the breakfast was delivered to the room each morning and there was a choice of various continental breakfast items, so that was good.The area the hotel was in left something to be desired but we had been warned about it by the travel agent that booked it for us. The civic area is close by and they're in the process of building a huge new government building a stones throw from the hotel but that doesn't seem to do anything for the area. The hotel offers a shuttle service into the shopping area and looking at a map we couldn't really understand why as the main city centre wasn't far. After our first walk into the city we knew why! Numerous people hanging around the streets, some begging for money, many being loud and swearing at people as they walked past etc. Not nice and we certainly wouldn't have done the walk after dark.The hotel is a bit out of the way for the main tourist areas by the water (pier 39, alcatraz etc.) but it is easily accessible using the shutle bus and the San Francisco trolly bus which is an experience in itself!	
