Apr 30 2006	my pick to stay	A small hotel with its own parking place. Off the street, a short walk from Market Street where there is much transportation that will take you anywhere,. I was impressed by the staff, kind, courteous. They made me feel so welcome as I entered the tiny lobby.They provide complimentary breakfast delivered daily to your room and a free shuttle to Union Square daily. The morning I checked out for an early trip to the airport, the clerk made sure my shuttle would be there to take me. I am elderly and traveling solo so it was a very pleasant experience for me to stay there. This is where I will stay again on my next trip to San Francisco.	
Aug 27 2005 	Nice inside the area couls be better	I stayed there for 5 nights on business. I was looking for a decent place with continental breakfast and free high-speed Internet for about $100/night, a tall order for San Francisco (in fact I paid an average of $111/night plus tax). There are 3 Best Westerns and the Hotel Britton on the same block, all with common ownership, and my impression from looking at them as I walked by is that the Carriage Inn was the nicest of the bunch. (The Flamingo is a motel, the Americania has outdoor corridors and the Britton was probably 75-80 years old.) If you try to make a reservation online and it says they are sold out, try calling. That's what happened to me and I was able to get a room.The room was nice and clean and what I would expect from a mid-priced hotel. The place appears to have been recently renovated. The high-speed Internet, however, is not wireless and you must bring your own Ethernet cable to plug into the data port, which happens to be located on the phone. I had a deluxe executive room and the desk was on the opposite side of the room from the phone. I brought a 14' cable with me and it was barely long enough to reach to the desk. So if you come here, bring a 25' cable. Also it says on the hotel's web site that the executive rooms have cordless phones, which is not true. The phone is corded and next to the bed. There's another phone in the bathroom (I've never really seen the point of that...) I had a room overlooking the spa area (instead of the street) and it was very quiet at night.The neighborhood, however, is rather dodgy. I'm a big guy from another big city so I didn't feel intimidated or threatened on the street after dark but you might think twice about staying here if you are with children. There are a lot of interesting characters on the street at all times of day. There aren't many places to eat in the area or grocery stores (plenty of liquor stores though). SOMA Pizza is OK, and there's the Peppers across the street at he Americania but I didn't eat there. The Chinese/Vietnamese place next door has good food and friendly service. Otherwise, don't bother walking around this neighborhood looking for food. I tried and was unsucessful. Wherever you are going in the city, you might as well eat dinner before returning to the hotel.It's easy to get to public transportation, with buses on Mission and on Howard and the Civic Center BART/Muni station is a block and a half away. I used public transport the entire time I was there, including getting to and from the airport. Overall it's a very good value for the money and I would stay there again.	
Aug 8 2005	Excellent breakfast clean accommodation 	We picked this hotel due to its close proximity to Union Square. The roooms have all the facilities you need; coffee machine, fridge, air con &amp; tv and clean and spacious. The free breakfast is excellent and delivered to your room every morning at the time you requested. We had read on this site that the area was a little dodgy but we encountered no problems, however, we were careful. There are another 3 Best Westerns in close proximity and I know one of them had a pool that we could have made use of. There is underground secure parking which we made use of once we had picked up our hire car. Would stay here again if we went to San Francisco again as its a perfect base for exploring the city. I didn't feel that we should have stayed in Fisherman's Wharf area although this is much prettier than the area we stayed in but I guess its more expensive too, although I didn't check this.	
Jun 22 2005	Enjoyed our stay	My boyfriend and I stayed at this hotel for three nights from 6/16 to 6/19. The hotel is really nice and the front desk clerk, Josette is just wonderful! We got in right about lunchtime and she recommended Sonoma pizza, which was about a 1/2 a block up. The pizza was great! Anyway, I digress, the hotel itself is nice, but I don't recommend that you stay here with your family. It is a pretty good hike to get to the tourist spots like the Warf, Lombard street, Coit Tower, etc. You can catch the F bus, which is only about a block up, but in the evenings the area is somewhat questionable. As a female, I don't think I would have been comfortable walking around by myself after dark. Overall we had a good experience with the hotel itself, parking wasn't a problem, the staff was great, the room was clean &amp; spacious and there was plenty of hot water. Oh, I do recommend that you ask for a room in the back of the building though.	
Jun 7 2005	Lovely Hotel at Bargain Price	This was very good value for money. The room was huge, and included a lounge and small dining area, plus a fridge and large bathroom. It was quite clean indeed. Breakfast was a change from the usual bagel they usually offer you downstairs, and it was nice to have it brought to the room. There is also a very pleasant patio area on the 2nd floor, with spa, which nobody but us appeared to use!Granted, 7th St isn't a fantastic location, but as others have said, if you're used to big cities, it won't really bother you much. There are a lot of homeless people in this area, but we walked back to the hotel on 7th late at night from the F-Line (2 blocks), and it was fine.Transport links from here are fab. F-Line streetcar to Castro/Fisherman's Wharf, less than 10 minute walk (or take the hotel's free shuttle) to cable cars and Union Sq. BART is two blocks away.We'd definitely go back.	
May 29 2005	Comfortable room Uncomfortable area!!	Best Western Carriage Inn is a &quot;nice&quot; little inn. Nice rooms, usually pleasant staff, and offers an okay complimentary breakfast. The inn is not in a central location. So, getting to fisherman's wharf and other tourist attractions is far and expensive, if you you are not driving. Some of the front desk staff do not give great directions and can be rude at times. When we checked out the girl at the front desk never said good bye and did not thank us for staying at &quot;The Best Western Carriage Inn&quot;. This made my boyfriend and I feel like we weren't worth the the girl's time and effort at all. This surronding location of the hotel is unpleasent and can make one feel unsafe at times, especially during the evening. The hotel is not near anything at all, but homeless people and loud traffic, depinding where your hotel room is located &quot;a good night's sleep&quot; is almost imposible with very loud traffic. Thus, since the hotel is not near anything, the hotel does offer a complimentary shuttle to Union's Square. The complimentary shuttle is the best feature of this hotel and made things a lot easier for us to get around the city since we both used public transportation and cabs to get from one place to the other. If I could go back and change anything from our trip to San Francisco, I would have stayed somewhere else that near by Fisherman's warf. Since, Fisherman's Wharf is where we spent most of our time and is near bt all the other tourist attractions, so it is a good idea to stay at a hotel near by that area. I can say the only very nice and helpful front desk clerk is josiet, she was always helpful and very nice with the both of us.	
May 19 2005	Nice hotel	The hotel is nice, but not great. The room was clean and large. The service is good but could be better. The area is questionable. I would not go walking after dark. It is central to tourist areas. Getting to fishermans warf take the F-line ($1.25 per person) from Market street (2 blocks up from hotel) and the ride is about 10 min. Breakfast is brought to your room every morning and is ok. Parking is $15.00us per day. Overall the stay was nice.	
Jan 13 2005	Great place to stay	In late December 2004, We had a wonderful stay at the Carriage Inn. It is really a bargain! The rooms are nice and spacious. The hotel is clean and comfortable. Having a continental breakfast delivered to the room, which is included in the room price, was a wonderful touch. Now if you aren't comfortable getting around in San Francisco or any big city, the neighborhood might cause you some concern. We never had any problems walking from the hotel to our destinations. However, its pretty obvious that you would not want to walk around the neighborhood late at night and the front desk will tell you the same thing. The hotel has a shuttle that runs to Union Square and taxis are easy to get. $15 a day for parking at the hotel is a major bargain! If you are a little adventurous, don't need to be right on top of Union Square, and want to be fairly close to downtown this is a great hotel!	
