Sep 14 2004	Top Notch	My wife and I made a trip to Frisco to catch the Falcons play the 49ers. My wife liked the way the Carriage looked online so we went ahead and reserved. We were suprised at how nice and well kept the hotel was. We were in a very central location and the hotel provided a shuttle that took us to and from the shopping area of Union Square. The breakfast that was brought to the room was very convenient, not to mention it was free. The parking was cheap, I paid more at the stadium. We had an excellent dinner at their restaurant that was located across the street. All the staff we came in contact with were very pleasant. Overall I would say this was one of my most pleasant traveling experiences. I look forward to returning the next time I go to San Fran.	
Sep 11 2004	May 2004	I did get an employee discount, so I'm unsure of how the rates compare to the service... but if their prices compare to their service, they must be EXPENSIVE.We stays a 4 day weekend, and the location was the only problem. Though only a few blocks from Union Square, there was a lot of construction, TONS of homeless people, and at night it was very quiet. It was a lil freaky, but we walked everywhere for 4 days, and simply got used to it. The &quot;bad&quot; area was only the few blocks around the hotel, after that, it was all businesses/shops. There are 3 separate hotels on each corner that are all Best Westerns. The Carriage Inn did not have a pool, but we were able to across the street and use theirs.The public transportation in San Fran is fantastic... do not rent a car ever! Parking and traffic is no fun. We took the bart train from the airport to downtown, where we could take a subway with a stop only 2 blocks from the hotel. We also took a cab once, buses, and the cablecars... when you buy any of the passes, the price is well worth.Service, wonderful. Front Desk was always helpful with a smile.. very small place, but the rooms were fantastic and gorgeously decorated. Free delivered breakfast, how can you beat that? If you don't have moola dollars, stay here and be treated like you do! If you do -- stay here, and save some cash from overexposed places...	
